      "content": "i get what u mean about the western bias thing, but like, looking at history objectively, it's hard to ignore that highly industrialized nation-states have objectively more power and global influence. wouldn't you say that the level of technological and administrative advancement in places like Europe or North America represents a more \"evolved\" or successful stage of human social organization compared to, say, tribal groups in the amazon or africa?",
